Description: Small fragment of a seal-impression, the fine brown Nile clay has some mica inclusions and was hardened after excavation. The rear shows a slightly concave impression of wood with string impression almost perpendicular to the wooden object, probably from a bolt or knob of a box. The front is covered in finger impressions, a small part of a seal impression is preserved, showing a circumferential line and several lines of signs that are not recognisable anymore.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E14.7 temple magazine
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
